\section{Tools}{


The MCP server exposes the following tools to Claude:

\describe{
\item{\code{auth_status}}{Check connection and field policy status.}
\item{\code{list_entities}}{List all available SELMA entity types with
descriptions.}
\item{\code{search_entities}}{Search entity types by keyword (case-insensitive,
matches name and description).}
\item{\code{describe_entity}}{Get per-column summary statistics for an entity.
Returns aggregates only — never individual rows.}
\item{\code{get_entity_summary}}{Get filtered/grouped aggregate statistics.
Supports \code{filter_by} and \code{group_by} parameters.}
\item{\code{get_efts_report}}{Generate an EFTS funding report by source and
category for a given year.}
\item{\code{execute_r}}{Execute R code in a sandboxed workspace with dplyr,
tidyr, ggplot2, lubridate, and scales. Variables persist between calls.
Code is inspected before execution — namespace access and I/O functions
are blocked.}
}
}

\section{PII Protection (7 Defence Layers)}{


Student data is sensitive. The server enforces:

\enumerate{
\item \strong{ID pseudonymisation} — session-scoped deterministic hashing of
all ID columns.
\item \strong{AST code inspection} — blocked packages and functions in
\code{execute_r}.
\item \strong{Input allowlisting} — only the 7 tools above are exposed; no raw
API access.
\item \strong{PII field policy} — configurable YAML allowlist controls which
columns are visible per entity (see \code{inst/mcp/field_policy.yml}).
\item \strong{Hybrid data access} — structured tools return aggregates only,
never individual rows.
\item \strong{Output scanning} — regex and PII dictionary checks on all
responses before they leave the server.
\item \strong{Audit logging} — JSONL log of every tool call plus a session
summary report.
}
}

